                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d318">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">548.D1/240: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-29T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 29, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>158. Department’s 385, October 10, 1934, 8 p.m.<note n="73" xml:id="d318fn73">
                        <ref target="frus1934v02#pg_316">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1934, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 316</ref>.</note> Please designate
                        Johnson<note n="74" xml:id="d318fn74">Herschel V. Johnson.</note> or other
                    member of your staff to act as American representative at meeting of Governing
                    body of High Commission for German refugees to open in London July 17 in lieu of
                    Chamberlain who will not be present. In case technical questions involving
                    immigration should be raised you may call on a competent member of the consulate
                    general. This Government has no objection in principle to concentration of
                    general refugee work under League. No other instructions believed necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
